<div id="review_1015793783" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1015793783" />
    <a title="Suliman" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/22192467-suliman"><img alt="Suliman" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1414858984p2/22192467.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1015793783?book_show_action=true">Aug 03, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Suliman" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Suliman" href="/user/show/22192467-suliman">Suliman</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/22192467-suliman?shelf=religion-and-philosophy">religion-and-philosophy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1015793783" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8578840124788815625">I had expected to read something more of a scientific than this. It&apos;s true that the author mentioned that it&apos;s a book of his own conversion experience from Islam &quot;which I liked it a bit&quot;, but I really had big expectations! Instead of him talking about facts and arguments about religion, and the troubles he had to face when he confronted his Islamic community, he talks about his &quot;literally&quot; childhood memories and a little bit of racism he had to face as a brown Bangladeshi child in UK. And when h</span>
  <span id="freeText8578840124788815625" style="display:none">I had expected to read something more of a scientific than this. It's true that the author mentioned that it's a book of his own conversion experience from Islam "which I liked it a bit", but I really had big expectations! Instead of him talking about facts and arguments about religion, and the troubles he had to face when he confronted his Islamic community, he talks about his "literally" childhood memories and a little bit of racism he had to face as a brown Bangladeshi child in UK. And when he mentions some arguments, at last, he just make quotations from greater authors! And he focuses on 2 or 3 of them such as Sam Harris, Daniel Dennett, and Richard Dawkins. I don't see how this book can be called "a young atheist's handbook"!!</span>
  <a data-text-id="8578840124788815625" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


